<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Section 8 Notice - Service and Validity Checklist</title>
  <style>
    {{{print_css}}}

    /* ===== @PAGE OVERRIDE - NARROW MARGINS ===== */
    /* Override print.css defaults to match Form 6A narrow margins */
    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 10mm;
    }

    /* Zero out body padding since @page handles margins */
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      color: #333;
    }
    h1 {
      color: #1a1a1a;
      border-bottom: 3px solid #2563eb;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    h2 {
      color: #2563eb;
      margin-top: 30px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      /* Keep heading with following content */
      page-break-after: avoid;
      break-after: avoid-page;
    }
    h3 {
      color: #1a1a1a;
      margin-top: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      /* Keep heading with following content */
      page-break-after: avoid;
      break-after: avoid-page;
    }
    .section {
      margin: 25px 0;
      /* Prevent section from being split across pages */
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .info-box {
      background: #f3f4f6;
      border-left: 4px solid #2563eb;
      padding: 15px;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }
    .warning {
      background: #fef3c7;
      border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b;
      padding: 15px;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }
    .checklist {
      background: #f9fafb;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 5px;
      margin: 20px 0;
      /* Prevent checklist from being split across pages */
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .checkbox {
      display: inline-block;
      width: 18px;
      height: 18px;
      border: 2px solid #333;
      margin-right: 10px;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }
    ul {
      margin-left: 20px;
      list-style: none;
    }
    li {
      margin: 12px 0;
    }
    .field-label {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #1a1a1a;
    }
    footer {
      margin-top: 50px;
      padding-top: 20px;
      border-top: 2px solid #e5e7eb;
      font-size: 0.9em;
      color: #6b7280;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Section 8 Notice - Service and Validity Checklist</h1>

  <div class="info-box">
    <strong>Purpose:</strong> Use this checklist to verify your Section 8 notice was served correctly and meets all validity requirements. Keep this checklist with your evidence file.
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Notice Details</h2>
    <p><span class="field-label">Landlord:</span> {{landlord_full_name}}</p>
    {{#if landlord_address}}
    <p><span class="field-label">Landlord Address:</span> {{landlord_address}}</p>
    {{/if}}
    <p><span class="field-label">Tenant:</span> {{tenant_full_name}}</p>
    <p><span class="field-label">Property Address:</span> {{property_address}}</p>
    <p><span class="field-label">Tenancy Start Date:</span> {{tenancy_start_date_formatted}}</p>
    <p><span class="field-label">Notice Service Date:</span> {{service_date_formatted}}</p>
    <p><span class="field-label">Earliest Possession Date:</span> {{earliest_possession_date_formatted}}</p>
    {{#if grounds}}
    <p><span class="field-label">Grounds:</span> {{ground_descriptions}}</p>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Service Evidence Checklist</h2>
    <div class="checklist">
      <p><strong>Confirm you have collected and retained the following evidence of service:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Original signed Section 8 notice (Form 3)</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Copy of the notice served to tenant</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Date and time of service recorded</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Method of service documented (hand delivery / first class post / recorded delivery)</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Proof of service:
          <ul style="margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 8px;">
            <li>If hand delivered: Photo of letterbox with notice visible, witness statement</li>
            <li>If posted: Proof of postage receipt from Royal Mail</li>
            <li>If recorded delivery: Tracking number and delivery confirmation</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Witness details recorded (name, address, signature) if applicable</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Any correspondence from tenant acknowledging receipt</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="warning">
      <strong>Keep All Evidence:</strong> You must prove service in court. Without clear evidence, your claim may be dismissed even if the notice is otherwise valid.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Validity Requirements (Housing Act 1988, Section 8)</h2>
    <div class="checklist">
      <p><strong>Verify your notice meets these validity requirements:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Notice uses correct form (Form 3 or substantially similar)</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> All mandatory fields completed (landlord name/address, tenant name, property address)</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Ground(s) for possession clearly stated with particulars</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Notice period is sufficient for the grounds claimed:
          <ul style="margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 8px;">
            <li><strong>60 days (2 months) minimum:</strong> Grounds 1, 2, 5, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11, 16</li>
            <li><strong>14 days (2 weeks) minimum:</strong> Grounds 3, 4, 7A, 7B, 8, 12, 13, 14, 14ZA, 15, 17</li>
            <li><strong>Immediate (0 days):</strong> Ground 14A (domestic violence), Ground 14 (serious ASB only)</li>
            <li><strong>Multi-ground notices:</strong> Use the MAXIMUM notice period across all selected grounds</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        {{#if is_fixed_term}}
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Fixed term tenancy: Notice only valid if tenancy agreement allows possession during fixed term, or fixed term has ended</li>
        {{else}}
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Periodic tenancy: Notice period calculated correctly from rent payment date</li>
        {{/if}}
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Notice signed and dated by landlord or landlord's agent</li>
        {{#if has_mandatory_ground}}
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Mandatory ground claimed: Court must grant possession if ground is proven (Grounds 1-8)</li>
        {{else}}
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Discretionary ground(s) claimed: Court will consider reasonableness (Grounds 9-17)</li>
        {{/if}}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>After Service</h2>
    <div class="checklist">
      <p><strong>Post-service actions:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Wait until possession date has passed: <strong>{{earliest_possession_date_formatted}}</strong></li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Do not change locks or remove tenant belongings (illegal eviction)</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Do not harass tenant or cut off utilities</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> If tenant remains after possession date, apply to court using Form N5 or N5B</li>
        <li><span class="checkbox"></span> Keep proof of service readily accessible for court</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer>
    <p><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Housing Act 1988, Section 8 and Schedule 2</p>
    <p><strong>Generated:</strong> {{generated_date}}</p>
    <p><strong>Landlord Heaven Notice Only Pack</strong> | England</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
